            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Why is the horizontal scroll not needed? It clearly looks needed to me?\n\nBecause:\n\n1. The text after applying `io` and `ik` is the same as built-in `i\"`, while the `iu` is essentially the same. The text fits into the available horizontal space, but for `io` and `ik` there is a scroll while `iu` and `i\"` there is none.\n2. The textobject that maps directly to the built-in `i\"` (i.e. `iu` in this example) shows the intended behavior without horizontal scrolling. And as the output is essentially the same as the other two, I'd expect the other two to also behave the same. I.e. the cursor movement that is done during the Operator-pending mode should not result in horizontal scrolling.\n\n> Also, what's the magic number 49 for?\n\nTo concisely mimic the behavior of `vi\"` in Opertor-pending mode in this particular case. It moves cursor outside of the view. For it to work precisely, the amount of available horizontal space has to not be very large (I've updated the code to also include `set column=191`) or there has to be more vertical splits.",
