        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> If you move the cursor off the screen then obviously you get a scroll. What you need here is a way to set the other end of the visual selection without actually moving the cursor there.\n\nThe difference is that the cursor is moved outside of view temporarily and only technically. The next redraw happens after applying the textobject and the final result doesn't require the scroll.\n\nSetting visual selection without moving cursor might make it less of an issue, but I think won't fix it 100%. Mostly because the cursor must be on either end of the visual selection, so there might be scroll in the other direction if the left end is outside of view. Although it seems that `ci\"` also leads to a scroll in this case.",
